q1: False.
In ANSI-C not all functions are global.
Each function can call only functions that
above her, unless there's a prototype declaration which allows all functions
in the same file to call each other.

q2: True.

If the file is not a directory, the size will be print.
If the file is a directory fsize() will call dirwalk() which then go through all
the files in the directory recursivly and call fsize() on them. 
